cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper is about using deep learning for medical image segmentation, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The proposed method involves using a context encoder network, which is a type of neural network architecture, and thus could also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on 2D medical image segmentation, which could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper involves using a pretrained ResNet block and other advanced techniques, which could also be categorized under neural networks (cs.NE) category.
